SAMPLES.DESCRIPTION: An example report returned in JSON format

PARAMETERS.NAME: reportID
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: ReportID of the saved report to run.

PARAMETERS.NAME: filterOverride
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION:
Override the standard filter value(s):
e.g: To override the Enrolment Status Value you can pass:
[{NAME:'enrolments.enrolstatus', VALUE:'canc', VALUE2:''}]
NOTE: You cannot test/use this in our API relax console simulator

PARAMETERS.NAME: displayLength
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: a.k.a 'pageSize' - Warehoused reports only: The maximum supported value is 1000. The number of row objects to return in the data[] response element. This should be used in conjunction with offsetRows to page through data. Wait for a response before calling the next page of data.

PARAMETERS.NAME: offsetRows
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: Warehoused reports only: The number of report rows to skip before returning row objects in the data[] response element. The maximum supported value is 100,000. Reports larger than this are not supported

DESCRIPTION: Interacts with the aXcelerate Report Builder to run a specified saved report. It will return the results in JSON format.
